cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.IR 

This paper is about training social dialogue systems using neural ranking techniques. The most relevant sub-category is likely to be cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and optimization, which could place it under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
